026 and propose a meeting to discuss the event’s programs.\\n\\nBefore I finalize the draft (and before sending it, if you’d like), could you please provide a few details?\\n\\n1. **Recipient email addresses** – the exact addresses for Mr. Frey and Anna.  \\n2. **Subject line** you’d like to use (e.g., “Planning Meeting for the 2026 Flower Festival”).  \\n3. **Preferred date/time** for the meeting you’d like to propose (or a range of options).  \\n4. Any **specific points or agenda items** you want highlighted in the body (e.g., budget, vendor selection, marketing plan).\\n\\nOnce I have that information, I’ll write the email and, if you confirm, I can send it to both addresses. Let me know!\\nHuman: 1. email address of frey is freylee.28@gmail.com and anna is amberbambico.58@gmail.com\\n2. yes \\n3. date would be feb 14 at 2pm of afternoon\\n4. come up on your own about the topics\\nAI: Got it—thanks for the details! I have the recipient addresses and the proposed meeting time (February 14 at 2 PM). I just need a quick clarification before finalizing and sending:\\n\\n**Subject line:** You wrote “yes” for the subject. Would you like me to use a specific subject such as **“Planning Meeting for the 2026 Flower Festival”**, or do you have another wording in mind?\\n\\nOnce you confirm the subject (and give the go‑ahead), I’ll draft the full email and send it to both freylee.28@gmail.com and amberbambico.58@gmail.com. Let me know!\\nHuman: yes",{"lc":1,"type":"255","id":"256"},"openai/gpt-oss-120b",["257"],"System: You are an AI Email Assistant. Your role is to help users draft, improve, and send clear, professional emails based on their instructions.\\n\\nGuidelines:\\n\\nMaintain a polite and professional tone unless the user requests otherwise.\\n\\nAsk for missing details such as recipient, subject, or purpose if unclear.\\n\\nImprove grammar and clarity while keeping the user’s intent.\\n\\nKeep emails concise and well-structured.\\n\\nTool Usage:\\n\\nOnly send e